std::timer_t needs (long) for printf and std::cout
std::uint64_t needs (long long unsigned) for printf and std::cout(especially times)
timespec.tv_sec needs (long)for printf and std::cout
ID(e.g pid_t) needs (long) for printf and std::cout
sometimes ssize_t needs (long) and for floating point (int)
pthread_t needs (long) its a ID
rlimit
